TY  - JOUR
T1  - Educational Advances in the Metaverse: Boosting Learning Through Virtual and Augmented Reality and Artificial Intelligence
AN  - 3050304851
AB  - This work delves into the emerging field of the metaverse and its application in education, exploring how virtual and augmented reality technologies can transform teaching and learning methods. Focusing on aspects of educational effectiveness, security, privacy, accessibility, and inclusive design, the study provides a comprehensive analysis of the potential of the metaverse in the educational field. Through a methodology that combines quantitative and qualitative analyses, including ANOVA and Pearson’s correlation coefficient, we evaluate the impact of the metaverse on academic performance and student engagement. The results indicate significant improvements in knowledge retention, student engagement, and user satisfaction, evidencing the value of the metaverse as an immersive and engaging educational tool. The study also highlights the importance of security and privacy in virtual learning environments, with tests and audits confirming the robustness of the metaverse against various cyber threats. Additionally, particular emphasis is placed on accessibility and inclusive design, demonstrating how the metaverse can provide equal learning opportunities for all students, regardless of their abilities or background. The results show that the metaverse represents a promising opportunity to revolutionize education, offering a more interactive, personalized, and accessible environment
